Snow on the reliefs about 1,500 meters and rain at lower altitude. Pasquetta Day 2024 characterized by bad weather in Trentino Alto Adige and not ideal for the classic 'outdoor trip'. The snow falls copious on the slopes and on the ski slopes. It snows on the Dolomites, snows in the area of Madonna di Campiglio. On the mountain roads above all of the province of Bolzano the road is snowy. Six Dolomite steps were closed for reasons, Gardena, Pordoi, Fedaia, Valparola, Falzarego and Giau. The winter closing remains for Stelvio, Rombo, Pennes and Stalle.
&nbsp;
In Friuli the firefighters from 6.45 are engaged on the A23 motorway, at km 64, for a landslide after the Campiolo tunnel: the debris invaded the carriage, no vehicle hit by the rocks. The same firefighters report that the operation is underway and the highway is closed in both directions. &nbsp;&nbsp;Exundation of some torrents and excrements also to Edolo in Val Camonica. Firefighters report it to work with different teams: evacuate 15 people resident in a flooded area. Established a local control unit for the coordination of the intervention.&nbsp; Over 60 centimetres of snow and a slavine have isolated the municipality of Livigno, in Valtellina. The Foscagno Pass, in fact, has been closed for several hours to the circulation. Mayor Remo Galli posted a video on social media where he invites citizens and tourists to stay in houses and hotels.&nbsp;
&nbsp;
The bad weather, however, has the time. The weather will be in decided improvement, "in the second part of the week" with an "anti-cyclone robust by the weekend on good part of the Mediterranean. Spring ready to explode then in the first weekend of April when we will have sun prevailing all over Italy with dry weather conditions but above all temperatures well above the averages of the period. Positive abnormalities again of 8/10 degrees".

